# -*-perl-*-

=head1 NAME

_SPECTROSCOPY_MODE_ -- switches observation mode to spectroscopy

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This primitive switches the current observation mode to spectroscopy,
which allows for spectroscopy primitives to be used by the current
recipe/primitive regardless of the instrument's actual observation
mode.

=head1 AUTHORS

Stephen P. Todd (Edinburgh University/UKATC)

=head1 COPYRIGHT

Copyright (C) 1998-2002 Particle Physics and Astronomy Research
Council.  All Rights Reserved.

=cut

# Make the switch.
$Frm->uhdr("ORAC_OBSERVATION_MODE" => "spectroscopy");
